headlines.description: — The last time the Timberwolves won in Boston, Kevin Garnett was the starting center — for Minnesota. Alex Rodriguez was in spring training, trying to bounce back from the New York Yankees' historic collapse in the AL Championship Series against the...
headlines.shortLinkText: East-leading Celtics hold off West's best Timberwolves in OT, improve to 18-0 at home

headlines.description: — Keegan Murray scored 25 points, Domantas Sabonis had 24 points and 10 rebounds and the Sacramento Kings beat the Charlotte Hornets 123-98 on Wednesday night for their second straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Sabonis help Kings run past Hornets, 123-98

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama looked like the biggest playmaker in the world, setting up teammates with slick passes on the break and in the post.
headlines.shortLinkText: Victor Wembanyama has 1st NBA triple-double for Spurs in 130-108 victory over Pistons

headlines.description: — Myles Turner had 18 points and 13 rebounds and the Indiana Pacers’ overcame star guard Tyrese Haliburton's absence to beat the Washington Wizards 112-104 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Turner, Pacers overcome Haliburton's absence to beat Wizards 112-104

headlines.description: — This time, Jalen Johnson and the Atlanta Hawks finished a close win at home.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Johnson stars as Hawks outlast Embiid-less 76ers, 139-132 in overtime

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — The season is nearing the halfway point, and the Oklahoma City Thunder are barely outside of the top spot in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 28 points, Thunder use runs of 17-0 and 13-0 to beat Heat 128-120

headlines.description: — Coby White scored 30 points and Zach LaVine made a big 3-pointer with 1:46 left in overtime, helping the Chicago Bulls top the Houston Rockets 124-119 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White scores 30 points as the Chicago Bulls beat the Houston Rockets 124-119 in overtime

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry, Klay Thompson and the Golden State Warriors are getting booed at home. Frustrated fans are leaving the arena early with their team facing daunting deficits and being dealt lopsided losses.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jonas Valanciunas scores 21 points as Pelicans take early lead and beat Warriors 141-105

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson had 27 points and nine assists to send the Utah Jazz past the Denver Nuggets 124-111 on Wednesday night for their ninth victory in 11 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson scores 27 points to help the surging Jazz beat the Nuggets 124-111

headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard, George score 29 apiece as Clippers rally in fourth quarter to defeat Raptors 126-120
